": 2681, \"to\": 2692}, {\"ngram\": \"THE WATER\", \"from\": 2696, \"to\": 2705}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris has built an underground reservoir designed to hold 46,000 cubic metres of runoff water during a storm, preventing the runoff flooding the city's antiquated sewage network and allowing untreated waste to flow into the Seine.\", \"from\": 2708, \"to\": 2938, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2708, \"end\": 2713, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3811566979912588e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2932, \"end\": 2937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999986016519, \"rank\": 1.3985144885330577e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an underground reservoir\", \"from\": 2724, \"to\": 2748}, {\"ngram\": \"46,000 cubic metres\", \"from\": 2766, \"to\": 2785}, {\"ngram\": \"runoff water\", \"from\": 2789, \"to\": 2801}, {\"ngram\": \"a storm\", \"from\": 2809, \"to\": 2816}, {\"ngram\": \"the runoff\", \"from\": 2829, \"to\": 2839}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's antiquated sewage network\", \"from\": 2849, \"to\": 2885}, {\"ngram\": \"untreated waste\", \"from\": 2899, \"to\": 2914}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Once the water is collected in the Austerlitz basin - a monster, 30-metre (98-feet) deep structure the size of a dozen Olympic swimming pools - it will be directed to a treatment plant before pouring into the Seine.\", \"from\": 2940, \"to\": 3155, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2975, \"end\": 2985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\", \"score\": 0.997517594355529, \"rank\": 0.002488583254947156, \"text\": \"Austerlitz\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Aus